						<summary>

						<p>Slab setup near the temple of Basavaṇṇa.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">9th-10th century A.D.</hi> </p>						

						<p>It probably registered a gift of 50 <hi rend="italic">mattar</hi> land and money [a portion of income from <hi rend="italic">siddhāya</hi> tax]. The beginning part of the slab are cut and lost. It is in characters of the 9th-10th century A.D.</p>						

